'''Otto Cuntz''' (10 September 1865, [[Stettin]] &ndash; 1 December 1932, [[Graz]]) was a German-Austrian classical historian, who specialized in ancient [[geography]] and [[topography]].
He studied at the universities of [[University of Zurich|Zurich]], [[University of Strasbourg|Strasbourg]] and [[University of Bonn|Bonn]], where his instructors were [[Heinrich Nissen]], [[Franz Bücheler]] and [[Hermann Usener]]. After graduation in 1888, he continued his education in [[University of Berlin|Berlin]] as a student of [[Otto Hirschfeld]] and [[Reinhard Kekulé von Stradonitz]]. In 1892 he took an extended study trip to Italy, Greece, Spain and France, then in 1894 obtained his [[habilitation]] at the University of Strasbourg. In 1898 he became an associate professor, and six years later was appointed a full professor of [[Roman history]] at the [[University of Graz]]. In 1920 he became a corresponding member of the [[Austrian Academy of Sciences]].<ref>[http://www.deutsche-biographie.de/pnd117666149.html Cuntz, Albert Hermann Otto] In: Neue Deutsche Biographie (NDB). Band 3, Duncker & Humblot, Berlin 1957, {{ISBN|3-428-00184-2}}, S. 440</ref> == Published works == * ''De Augusto Plinii Geographicorum auctore''. Bonn 1888 (dissertation). * ''Agrippa und Augustus als Quellenschriftsteller des Plinius in den geographischen Büchern der Naturalis historia''. In: Jahrbücher für classische Philologie. 17. Supplementband (1890), S. 473–527 &ndash; [[Marcus Vipsanius Agrippa|Agrippa]] and [[Augustus]] as sources for [[Pliny the Elder|Pliny]] in the geographical books of [[Naturalis Historia]]. * ''Beiträge zur Textkritik des Itinerarium Antonini''. In: Wiener Studien. Band 15 (1893), S. 260–298 &ndash; Contribution to the textual criticism of the [[Antonine Itinerary]]. * ''Patrum Nicaenorum nomina Latine Graece Coptice Syriace Arabice Armeniace'', 1898 (edited with [[Heinrich Gelzer]] and Heinrich Hilgenfeld). * ''Polybius und sein Werk'', 1902 &ndash; [[Polybius]] and his works. * ''Die Geographie des Ptolemaeus, Galliae, Germania, Raetia, Noricum, Pannoniae, Illyricum, Italia. Handschriften, Text und Untersuchung'', 1923 &ndash; The geography of [[Ptolemy]], [[Gaul]], [[Germania]], [[Rhaetia]], [[Noricum]], [[Pannonia]], [[Illyricum (Roman province)|Illyricum]], Italy. Handwritings, text and investigations.<ref>[https://de.wikisource.org/wiki/Otto_Cuntz Otto Cuntz] de.Wikisource</ref> == References == {{reflist}}
