{{Geo-term-stub}}

'''Tuškanac''' is a neighborhood located in [[Gornji Grad - Medveščak]] city district of [[Zagreb]], [[Croatia]]. It has a population of 2,455 (2011).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zagreb.hr/default.aspx?id=14356|title=12. Mjesni odbor Tuškanac|accessdate=11 January 2015}}</ref> It is best known for its parks and the Tuškanac cinema.

Apparently, its name derives from the name of [[Tuscany]]. It is assumed that it refers to Tuscan immigrants to Zagreb, some of whom have been recorded in the 14th century.<ref>"The great-grandson of Dante Alighieri, Nicolò, founded the first pharmacy in Zagreb in 1395." http://www.croatianhistory.net/etf/dante.html Located in Kamenita street in today's Gornji Grad</ref>

